	     MORE than 40 original works of art will be exhibited at a festival of talent, beauty and timeless artistry at the Margate Art Museum from November 4. Organisers said the exhibition, which runs for a month, is not to be missed.  The free entry grand opening at the Margate Art Museum will start at 5pm on November 4 and patrons are asked to come dressed in smart casual. “It is an opportunity to get away from the rush of daily life and get lost in the majestic works created by top local artists. All the works on exhibition are available for purchase,” said Lelane Bouwer. “We hope to see everyone on the 4th of November for a spectacular evening that will satisfy even the most ravenous artistic curiosity,” said Bouwer. “Come and enjoy a festive night with drinks, snacks, fire dancing and drumming,” she said.  For more information, contact Margate Art Museum on 039 312 8392. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  